  "prompt": "What is iTunes?",
  "response": "iTunes is a media player, media library, online radio broadcaster, and mobile device management application developed by Apple Inc. Originally released in 2001, it was primarily used for playing, downloading, and organizing digital music and video files. Key features included:\n\n1. Music and media library management\n2. Purchasing and downloading music, movies, TV shows, and apps from the iTunes Store\n3. Syncing media and files with Apple devices like iPods, iPhones, and iPads\n4. Backing up and restoring iOS devices\n5. Podcast and audiobook management\n\nIn recent years, Apple has phased out iTunes, replacing it with separate apps like Apple Music, Apple TV, and Finder on Mac computers for device management. However, it remains an important part of Apple's digital media history.",
